organic_results.title: Does consistency of parental educational encouragement matter for secondary school students?
organic_results.snippet: Relationships between parental educational encouragement and adolescents' college activity are examined in a four wave longitudinal data set with both males and females. These data contain a perceived parental encouragement measure at the ninth, tenth and twelfth grades, as well as respondents' actual educational activity in the year following high school graduation.
